In a previous post, Bruce 'Loodvrij' Keeler (loodvrij@cyb.fred.com) wrote:
: Actually, I think one good answer would be Calling Line ID services provided
: by the phone company (have they actually got round to allowing this?  I've
: not been paying much attention I'm afraid).  

It got bogged down in California and isn't available.

: The card company simply checks
: the calling phone number against a customer supplied list of valid numbers.
: It would mean the customer wouldn't be able to order from a payphone, but I
: can't see that that would be much disadvantage.

Without Caller ID, the card company can verify by calling you back at the
number you give them.  (Assuming it's a valid one on the list.)
